President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Thomas J. Curry as Comptroller of the Currency at the Department of the Treasury. Curry has served on the Board of Directors of the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation since 2004 and has experience in state government as well. 

Mary John Miller has been nominated as Under Secretary for Domestic Finance at the Department of the Treasury. She has been serving as the Assistant Secretary for Financial Markets since 2010 and has extensive experience in the financial industry.

Wendy R. Sherman has been nominated as Under Secretary for Political Affairs at the Department of State. She has previously served as Counselor for the State Department and as President Clinton's Policy Coordinator on North Korea. She has also served on various commissions and boards related to national security and foreign policy.

President Obama has also announced his intent to appoint Rafael Anchía as a member of the Advisory Committee for Trade Policy and Negotiations. Anchía is a representative in the Texas House of Representatives and is also a partner at a law firm.

Carmen Lucca Nazario has been appointed as the United States Representative to the Executive Board of the United Nations Children's Fund (UNICEF). Nazario is an Assistant Professor in the School of Social Work and has served in various government positions related to children and families.